Issue Gathering:
- Document exact error message or behavior
- Identify the application name and version
- Determine when the issue started
- Ask about recent changes or updates

Initial Troubleshooting:
- Close and reopen the application
- Restart the computer
- Check if issue occurs for other users
- Verify network connectivity if cloud/network app

{% if app_type == 'office' %}
Microsoft Office Crashes:
- Run Office repair (Quick Repair first, then Online Repair)
- Disable COM add-ins one by one
- Start application in Safe Mode
- Update Office to latest version
- Check for conflicting antivirus settings
- Repair or recreate user profile
{% endif %}

{% if app_type == 'browser' %}
Browser Issues:
- Clear browser cache and cookies
- Disable extensions and test
- Reset browser to default settings
- Try incognito/private mode
- Update browser to latest version
- Try alternate browser
{% endif %}

{% if app_type == 'erp_crm' %}
Business Application Errors:
- Clear application cache
- Verify server/service status
- Check user permissions and roles
- Test in different browser if web-based
- Verify Java/runtime requirements
- Contact vendor support if persistent
{% endif %}

Log Analysis:
- Check Windows Event Viewer for errors
- Review application-specific logs
- Look for crash dump files
- Document error patterns

Advanced Resolution:
- Uninstall and reinstall application
- Check for Windows updates
- Verify system file integrity (sfc /scannow)
- Test with different user profile

Resolution:
- Document root cause and fix
- Update knowledge base with solution
- Notify user of resolution
- Monitor for recurrence
